@Devon Montgomery Specifically I got pretty deep into the Python 3 For Beginners course. It spent hours going into great detail about how each type of variable worked, which is probably useful information, but after about four hours I was still sort of just faffing about with a very user-unfriendly calculator without the ability to make anything anyone would consider useful.

Unlike this course, the instructor didn't really encourage you to try things on your own, which got pretty boring. I'd follow along in my editor, but it really wasn't necessary, as none of the problems he tackled were difficult (not that these are super difficult for someone above novice level, but I found the challenge here to be much better). 

There are other courses there that may be better, and for more advanced stuff, I'm sure there's some meat to be found, but that course was not great.﻿

